body:
I also think that the iterator might be broken, for example:

``` rust
let mut flags = collections::EnumSet::empty();
flags.add(InitJoystick);
flags.add(InitVideo);
flags.add(InitHaptic);
for flag in flags.iter() {
    println!("{}", flag);
}
```

Prints:

```
InitEverything
InitVideo
```

Of course that does not mean that the implementation could not be fixed.

@bjz: Macro rules currently can't disambiguate `#[$doc_attr:meta]` vs `$Flag:ident`*. Only a procedural macro could preprocess doc attributes and possibly pass everything to another macro definition.

My functionality is flawed. It doesn't let you write `FlagABC = FlagA.bits | FlagB.bits` at all.

\* `error: local ambiguity: multiple parsing options: built-in NTs ident ('Flag') or 1 other options.`

@bjz: this PR was discussed in the weekly meeting today, and consensus was that we should merge it, but as part of `libstd`.  This is because we want to be able to provide type-safe APIs in `libstd` that are C-compatible.  (Ultimately `libstd` and `libcollections` [are likely to be refactored](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/40) making this moot.)

We can improve the documentation aspect later on, once sufficient macro support is available.

Can you please update to move to `libstd` (and take care of any bitrot)?  Then we will review and merge.
